meanings.definition: To press out or squeeze out forcefully.
meanings.sent1: She outpresses the toothpaste tube to get every last bit out.
meanings.sent2: He always outpresses the sponge to remove excess water.
meanings.sent3: The chef outpresses the garlic to add flavor to the dish.
meanings.sent4: The athlete outpresses the juice from the orange like a champion.
meanings.sent5: The machine outpresses the oil from the olives efficiently.

meanings.definition: To surpass in pressing or squeezing out.
meanings.sent1: The new juicer outpresses all the old models in extracting juice.
meanings.sent2: She outpresses her competitors in getting the most juice from fruits.
meanings.sent3: The robot outpresses the humans in squeezing lemons for lemonade.
meanings.sent4: The powerful machine outpresses any manual effort in extracting liquids.
meanings.sent5: The hydraulic press outpresses any other method in extracting oils from seeds.
